This paper is primarily focused on neural networks and their performance on computer vision tasks, which suggests that it would likely fall under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of architecture search and pruning, which are common techniques in machine learning and could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also discusses the use of constant weights and the discovery of digital circuits, which could potentially place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) categories, respectively.
